{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C5q6Z3quLuLWWzwgUmDerv","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Baked Cod in Parchment.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1677a1a0-3dd2-4865-b5dd-2a17929d8d49","uuid":"e8de0b00-764b-474a-b845-40a73594a708","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Baked Cod in Parchment.generated.24.txt","content":"Baked Cod in Parchment\n\nThere's something magical about opening a parchment packet hot from the oven,\nreleasing a cloud of aromatic steam infused with herbs, white wine, and delicate\nfish. En papillote—cooking in parchment—is a classic French technique that has\nbeen passed down through generations of home cooks and professional chefs alike.\nThis elegant method requires minimal cleanup and delivers maximum flavor, as the\nfish gently steams in its own juices with vibrant vegetables. Tonight, bring\nthis restaurant-worthy technique to your table.\n\nPreparation Time: 15 minutes\nCooking Time: 18-20 minutes\nServes: 2\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n2 cod fillets, 6-8 oz each\n2 cups mixed vegetables (zucchini, bell peppers, carrots, julienned)\n3 cloves garlic, thinly sliced\n1/4 cup dry white wine\n2 tablespoons butter\n2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n2 sprigs fresh thyme\n2 sprigs fresh tarragon\nSea salt and freshly ground pepper\nParchment paper\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n\n2. Cut two large pieces of parchment paper (about 15x12 inches each).\n   Fold in half, then open.\n\n3. Divide vegetables between parchment sheets, arranging on one half\n   of each sheet.\n\n4. Place cod fillet on top of vegetables. Season with salt and pepper.\n   Top with garlic slices, herbs, and a dot of butter.\n\n5. Drizzle with wine and lemon juice.\n\n6. Fold parchment in half, sealing edges by folding and crimping.\n   Place on baking sheet.\n\n7. Bake 18-20 minutes. The parchment will puff up as it steams.\n\n8. Carefully open packets (watch for steam!) and serve immediately.\n\nWINE PAIRING: A crisp Sauvignon Blanc or Albariño enhances the delicate\nflavors of the fish without overpowering it.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
