{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TrVx6yA4LfFgE5tnJQ14td","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0169BammdxYs2ev4cAbP2ge2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Braised Lamb Shanks.generated.24.txt","content":"Braised Lamb Shanks\n\nWhen the weather turns cold and the days grow short, there's nothing more\ncomforting than a bowl of tender lamb, braised until it falls from the bone\nin a rich, deeply flavored sauce. This ancient cooking technique has been used\nfor centuries to transform tough cuts of meat into something transcendent through\nthe patient application of low heat and time. A whole shank requires several hours\nto cook, but the result is worth every minute—succulent, flavorful meat that needs\nnothing more than a fork to eat it. Serve with creamy mashed potatoes or crusty\nbread to soak up every precious drop of sauce.\n\nPrep Time: 15 minutes\nBraise Time: 3-3.5 hours\nServes: 4\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n4 lamb shanks (about 1.25 lbs each)\n3 tablespoons olive oil\n1 large onion, coarsely chopped\n4 large carrots, cut into 2-inch pieces\n4 celery ribs, cut into 2-inch pieces\n6 cloves garlic, smashed\n2 cups dry red wine\n4 cups beef or lamb stock\n3 tablespoons tomato paste\n4 sprigs fresh rosemary\n3 sprigs fresh thyme\n2 bay leaves\n1 teaspoon black pepper\n1.5 teaspoons salt\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 325°F (160°C).\n\n2. Pat lamb shanks dry and season generously with salt and pepper.\n\n3. Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Brown shanks\n   on all sides, about 3 minutes per side. Remove to a plate.\n\n4. In same pot, add onion, carrots, and celery. Cook 8-10 minutes until\n   they start to brown.\n\n5. Add garlic and tomato paste, cook 2 minutes more, stirring frequently.\n\n6. Deglaze with red wine, scraping up browned bits. Let simmer 5 minutes.\n\n7. Return lamb to pot. Add stock, rosemary, thyme, and bay leaves.\n\n8. Bring to simmer, cover, and transfer to oven. Braise 3-3.5 hours until\n   meat is very tender.\n\n9. Remove shanks to a platter. Strain braising liquid, skim fat if needed.\n\n10. Serve shanks with vegetables and sauce poured over top.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":88228,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":88228},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1677a1a0-3dd2-4865-b5dd-2a17929d8d49","uuid":"59235d0c-b9fd-48ea-8bdc-23a31b21e69e"}
